content.definition: This element describes a standard Australian Area Code as used in conjunction with telephone and facsimile numbers.  The 2-digit area code should be abbreviated to 1-digit when used in conjunction with leading country code. If this is the case, the leading ZERO in the area code should be removed.  E.g. 03 55551234 becomes 61 3 55551234.
content.name: Telephone Area Code Number

content.definition: The number that provides minimal designation of that is associated to a unique provision of telephone service as accessed locally through a standard dialling access. Australian telephone numbers are usually 6 to 10 digits in length and can be represented as numerals or letters that can be converted to their associated number.  Mobile telephone numbers: The first two digits of a mobile telephone number are officially the area code for mobile telephones in Australia. E.g. The mobile telephone area code for Australia is 04. For this standard we are defining the area code to be part of the mobile phone number, therefore no mobile phone numbers will have an associated area code.
content.name: Telephone Designation Number
